    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Forests with varied vegetation, depending upon whether they are tropical or temperate, but having in common a high annual rainfall of between 98-180 inches. Tropical rainforests are found closer to the equator and temperate rainforests are found farther north near coastal areas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
